{
  "recommendation": "For patients with SLCO1B1 Poor Function genotype, consider prescribing the lowest effective dose of pitavastatin (1 mg/day) or switching to a statin less sensitive to SLCO1B1 variation (e.g., fluvastatin or rosuvastatin at reduced doses). If pitavastatin is used, initiate at the lowest dose and monitor closely for signs and symptoms of myopathy (muscle pain, weakness, elevated CK). Avoid high doses of pitavastatin in this genotype.",
  "classification": "Moderate",
  "implication": "SLCO1B1 Poor Function (carrying the *15 allele, defined by c.521T>C / rs4149056) results in reduced hepatic uptake of pitavastatin via the OATP1B1 transporter, leading to approximately 76% higher systemic AUC and 122% higher Cmax compared to normal function carriers. This increased systemic exposure elevates the risk of statin-induced myopathy, including the rare but serious risk of rhabdomyolysis."
}
